text:
This movie isn't good. Let's just keep Brad Pitt out of Philadelphia to keep us all safe... Was the CIA guy also from 12 Monkeys? Yes, he was. 12 Monkeys is 💯×s better than WWZ. Just watch that again. (Apologies. I always struggle with ADHD when confronted with awful entertainment).WWZ ain't ALL bad... They spent plenty on the special-effects budget. Visually there's enough on which to feast, if you don't mind starving your other senses, especially your good sense. Here's some good sense violations: 1. Then they're not watching the walls in Jerusalem. Impossible. 2. He survives a plane crash. Just silly. 3. Send the guy with the shrapnel in his gut and the girl with one arm to retrieve the lab samples amidst 80 zombies. 4. Oh, Brad Pitt figures out how to fight the virus, when the world's top scientists cannot. What a hero. 5. I could go on. Dismissing the substandard nonsense that can show up in film comes down to personal taste. I think I have a medium tolerance, but when a threshold is breached I morph from tolerant to disgusted in a moment. I was disgusted before the half-way point.It seems that much of the plot was about working-in cool shots, as there's a lot of cool shots; but there's really no plot. That ain't cool. This is not optimal use of Brad Pitt either. I don't want to see Brad Pitt in a movie in which he's not snarky, or where we don't at least once hear that manic laugh. Some of their dramatic plot twists are almost funny, like the scientist dying by tripping... except it's not funny. It only feels empty. I don't like feeling empty. The only reason to watch this show is for a few clever special effects, but when has that ever been enough? I do enjoy a good zombie feature, but WWZ has too much rotting, festering decay to climb over in order to get to anything presentable.The list of better zombie features is too long to cite, but here's a smattering of recommendations:Resident Evil - Serious action;
Zombieland - Serious fun;
28 Days Later - Serious drama;
Shaun of the Dead - Serious laughs; and
I am Legend - Seriously, there's nothing wrong with that film. It's perfectly respectable.THE WALKING DEAD - This is about the family-we-choose fighting for survival;
The Last of Us - Serious science, serious drama, serious acting, serious introspection;
KINGDOM - Serious thrills and Detective work; and
Sweet Home - Seriously heart-wrenching and exciting.While I was looking up zombie features, I stumbled across a couple that I haven't seen yet, but these are immensely popular: ASH VS EVIL DEAD,
IN THE FLESH,
PUSHING DAISIES,
IZOMBIE,
DEAD SET, & SANTA CLARITA DIET. Perhaps watching some of these will cleanse the palate. I feel like I ate something bad.🐨
